  "text": "The most frequently encountered portfolio costs are transaction, commission, management, performance (liquidity) costs and taxes. Transaction costs may be constant (fixed) or proportional [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Fixed transaction costs increase with the diversification as the fixed costs vary with the number of assets in the portfolio. Hence the number of assets in the portfolio might decrease with the optimization [CITATION_3] . On the contrary, proportional transaction costs depend on the investment amount. Contrary to fixed costs, proportional transaction costs encourage the variety of tools included in the portfolio. Moreover, their shares decrease when the investment amount increases [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
